				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\alpha$$\end{document} emission from a Cu target. A divergence slit of 0.2 mm was placed in the input-beam path and an anti-scatter screen above the sample provided efficient measurements. The measurements were done with step resolution of 0.022˚ over the continuous 2-theta range of 10˚–70˚. The obtained spectrum was compared with that in the literature to determine the crystalline orientation of the measured face. Similar procedure was repeated along other flat faces of the crystal, and the corresponding orientation axis was determined.

